 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Even Such Is Time</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octave">
     <l n="1" met="--+-+-+-+">Even such is time, which takes in trust</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+-+-+">Our youth, our joys, and all we have,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+-+-+-+">And pays us but with age and dust;</l>
     <l n="4" met="+--+-+-+">Who in the dark and silent grave</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+-+-+-+">When we have wandered all our ways</l>
     <l n="6" met="++-+---+">Shuts up the story of our days;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+-+-+">And from which earth, and grave, and dust</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+-+">The Lord shall raise me up, I trust.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
